## 10. Recommended first task breakdown

1. Add committed NIAH generator / fixtures under `benchmarks/longctx/niah/`.
2. Add `pflash_compress_demo.rs` that accepts a token span sidecar and runs target prefill on compressed IDs.
3. Convert / load Qwen3-0.6B as a hipfire drafter artifact and validate tokenizer identity.
4. Add dense drafter Q/K capture for 8K-16K.
5. Implement CPU selector and establish quality curves for `keep_ratio={0.20,0.10,0.05}`.
6. Port scoring / selection to HIP kernels.
7. Port sparse drafter attention.
8. Wire daemon opt-in mode and memory lifecycle.
9. Run coherence + long-context validation gates.

Do not skip the quality curve. A 10x TTFT number is only meaningful if the compressed prompt still supports retrieval and normal answer quality across more than single-needle NIAH.
